<b>Couple corrections - </b>5/15/01 1:01:44 PM<br>~ <b>Jairren</b><blockquote>SoT moves the mob in the opposite of the direction the bard is facing.  Facing toward the mob pulls it to you; turning your back on it pushes it away.<br><br>SoT lasts longer than other bard songs - 5 ticks, not 3.<br><br>Useful note: SoT's magic resist debuff is quite significant when using a wind instrument, and stacks with Occlusion of Sound's debuff (which does not break the mez), knocking a total of more than 50 points off a mob's magic resist.  Great for landing a slow or a longer-lasting resist debuff.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
