<b>Explanation - </b>3/3/01 12:38:29 PM<br>~ <b>Melvyn Organgrinder</b><blockquote>Song of Twilight's &quot;knock forward&quot; effect is not exactly &quot;it knocks the target forward.&quot;  Instead, the message you get from the song is that &quot;Target&quot; stumbles towards you.  The target ACTUALLY moves in the OPPOSITE direction to which the bard is facing.  If the bard had his/her back to the target when the song hit, the target would be pushed backwards, or AWAY from the bard.  Complicated to explain, but easy to demonstrate in action.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Comments - </b>2/3/01 1:34:55 AM<br>~ <b>Rellic</b><blockquote>Doesn't require wind anymore, and it's more of a knock-forward effect than a knock-back =)<br><br><i>Kocho - Thanks, made the changes</i></blockquote></td></tr></table></blockquote><br><br><br><br>
